==English==

===Etymology===
From {{Sp.}} [[Canibalis]], the name given by Christopher Columbus to the Caribs of Cuba and Haiti who allegedly ate human flesh.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# An [[organism]] which [[eat]]s others of its own [[species]].

